author: @peanutgummybearwifeuwu8270
text:
Belly: So! Do you recognise any of these men?
Penny: I was hiding in the bathroom stall. I didn’t see his face but I heard him… He was singing in a bar.
Belly: What song do you think he was singing?
Penny: I think it was the song I Want It That Way?
Belly: Backstreet Bears I’m familiar. Okay number 1 can you please sing the opening to I Want It That Way?
Gummy: Really? Okay! You are my fire.
Belly: Number 2 keep it going.
Paperotti: The one desire.
Belly: Number 3.
Crazy: Believe when I say.
Belly: Number 4.
Vampiro: I want it that way.
Belly: Tell me why!
Gummy, Paperotti, Crazy and Vampiro: Ain’t nothing but a heartache.
Belly: Tell me why!
Gummy, Paperotti, Crazy and Vampiro: Ain’t nothing but a mistake.
Belly: Now number 5.
Vincent: I really wanna hear you say.
Belly: Yes!
Gummy, Paperotti, Crazy, Vampiro and Vincent: I want it that way!
Penny: It was number 5. Number 5 killed my brother.
Belly: *Oh my god I forgot about that.*

author: @KyoninArmy
text:
So, do you recognise any of these men?
I was hiding in the bathroom stall, so I

didn't see his face, but I heard him.
He was singing along to the music at the
bar.
Do you remember what he was singing?
I think it was that song, "I Want It
That Way"
Backstreet Boys, I'm familiar. Okay...
Number One, can you please sing the
opening to "I Want It That Way"?
Really? Okay.
You are my fire...
Number Two, keep it going...
The one desire...
Number Three...
Believe when I say...
Number Four...
I want it that way...
TELL ME WHY!
Ain't nothing but a heartache...

TELL ME WHY!
Ain't nothing but a mistake...
Now number five...

I never want to hear you say...
WOO!
I Want It That Way!

Ahh. Chills you guys.

Literal chills...
It was number five. Number five
killed my brother!
Oh my god, I forgot about that part!
Arranged by Dragons89
Brooklyn Nine-Nine continues
Thursdays at 9pm on NBC

And Number 5 killed my brother.

author: @blah__
text:
Yesterday night I was doing my French homework for today and I saw “you are = tu es” and I screen shotted and went onto google translate and searched up “my fire” in French. So then I took a screenshot of that and sent it to my friend (which perfectly was watching Brooklyn 99 earlier that day) and you know said it. Then she actually google translated the whole to French which was really nice of her and I said “omg we need to karaoke that” (which by we don’t actually don’t do karaoke) and she messaged me privately saying “go on the group chat in 10 mins” 10 minutes later she said “give me another 10 mins” another 10 minutes later I asked how long and she said “7 mins” I said “5 mins, more/less or none” she said 5 mins. 5 mins later I asked her “?” And she said it’s sending.

I went onto the group chat was confused and then she put the music on. She sang the whole song in French ☺️ best friend ever

Brooklyn 99 

Jake: "So, do you recognize any of these men?"

男「…では、誰がその男か、判るか？」
女「私はバスルームに隠れていたので、その男の顔は見ませんでした。しかし、彼の声は聞きました。バーで、音楽に合わせて歌っていたんです。」

author: @yngvildrthevoracious
text:
I just had the most satisfying evening woth some friends playing CAH : the question started by "why can't..." and I do'nt remember the rest but the card czar repeated "tell me why!" to which I of course followed with "ain't nothing but a heartache" sung on key...
Then a friend started to sing another "tell me why" on key and we continued... Then we all lost it when they sung "now number fiiiiiive!" and I managed to croak a "I never wanna hear you say" through laughter. It was on Discord so cue the discordant "what is time?"' "I waaaant iiiit that way!" the friend who started to clue me in on Brooklyn 99 started to say "It was number 5" to which half the group gasped in recognition. I then stuttered a "I entirely forgot about that" and then someone had to go to bed, the "Tell me why" card czar won the game and I really wish that life had a record button handy so that this moment could live on outside of our flawed memories.

author: @chl0522
text:
Person 1: "So- Do you recognize any of these men?"

Person 2: "I was hiding in the bathroom stall so I didn't see his face. But I heard him- He was singing along to the music of the bar- "

P1: "Do you remember what he was singing?"

P2: "Uhh- I think it was the song-- I want it that way?" 

P1: "Backstreetboys. Im familiar. Okay.. Number 1 can you sing the opening to "I want it that way?"

#1 "really?.. Okay-

You are my fire"

P1: "Number 2 keep going-" 

#2: "The one desire--"

P1: "Number 3.?"

#3: "Believe when I say"

P1: "Number 4!"

 #4: "I want it that way"

P1: "Tell me why!" 

Everyone: "Ain't nothin' but a heartache-"

P1: "Tell me why!" 

Everyone: "Ain't nothin' but a mistake-"

P1: "Now Number 5!-" 

#5: "I never want to hear you say-" 

P1: "WOAH"

Everyone: "I want it that way...!"

P1: "Ahh Chills. Literal Chills." 

P2: "It was Number 5. Number 5 killed my brother." 

P1: "Oh My God.... I forgot about that part..."

author: @Bedinsis
text: Given how funny this scene is, it's easy to overlook that the people on the line-up actually are acting. All but number 5 are either giving sideways glances as if they are thinking "is this for real" or are so stiff in their performance that they must be thinking "Fine, let's do this to get it over with". Number 5, though, actually is performing the song, both with his eyes, his hand and his facial expression. Which makes sense since it apparently is a song he enjoys enough that he sings along to it even while performing a murder.

author: @inmagab
text:
I’ve studied witness bias quite a lot for someone who’s not interested in criminology or anything similar lol and I have to say this seems like a really bad idea to actually recognize the murderer in this scenario. Since the witness was connected to the victim she’s very likely to want to find the culprit, and since she’s been given 5 people to ‘choose from’ she’ll likely choose one of them even if none of them actually committed the crime. Our sound memory isn’t actually that good, so he just might have a similar voice to the guy who killed his brother. I’d like to see how they made that line up and how they actually chose the suspects. 


PS yes I know this is a comedy and I loved the comedic value of this, I just have an exam on perception coming up and this just occurred to me as a good example of possible witness bias lol
